ional success. In this way, Green reveals Ibn Kaspi to be more than a mere commentator on texts, but a highly innovative thinker whose insights into the subtleties of the Bible produced a view of history that is both groundbreaking and original.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHistoryxPhilosophy. 0aJewish philosophy. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 4aHistory : Historiography. 4aHistory : Medieval Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Theology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847604940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438476049423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438476049/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles